main event: A freelance photographer in South Charleston, Ohio, submitted a report regarding the observation of unidentified flying objects captured in photographs on October 31, 1964.
interesting points: The photographer reported observing a circular object that seemed white or silver,The object was visible for about 10-15 minutes,The photographer claimed the object was not visible to him at the time of exposure,Analysis concluded that the photographic anomalies were likely caused by scratches or reflections in the negatives,The report highlighted that the images were not a result of trick photography as suspected by some individuals.
